# Styling Conventions

## SCSS Modules + Tailwind + Primer (Standard)

- ALL component styles in `<ComponentName>.module.scss`
- Every SCSS module MUST start with `@reference` to access Tailwind:

```scss
@reference "tailwindcss/theme";
@reference "tailwindcss/utilities";

.root {
  @apply flex flex-col items-center p-4 gap-2;
}
```

### Exception: `@use` before `@reference`

When a SCSS module needs `@use` (e.g., `@use '@/styles/breakpoints' as *` for responsive mixins), the SASS compiler **requires** `@use` to appear before all other rules — including `@reference`. This is a SASS language constraint, not a style violation. The correct order in this case is:

```scss
@use '@/styles/breakpoints' as *;
@reference "tailwindcss/theme";
@reference "tailwindcss/utilities";
```

Do NOT flag this as a violation during audits. It is the only valid order when `@use` is present.

- Import in component: `import styles from './ComponentName.module.scss'`

## Two Sources of Truth

| Category | Source | How |
|----------|--------|-----|
| Layout, spacing, sizing | Tailwind | `@apply flex p-4 gap-2 w-full` |
| Transitions, transforms | Tailwind | `@apply transition-all duration-200 ease-in-out` |
| Borders (width, radius) | Tailwind | `@apply rounded-md`, `border-right: 1px solid var(--borderColor-default)` |
| z-index | Tailwind | `@apply z-10 z-30 z-40` |
| Opacity, scale, display | Tailwind | `@apply opacity-70 scale-95 hidden block` |
| **ALL colors** | **Primer via useTheme** | `var(--primer-fg-default)`, `var(--primer-canvas-subtle)` |
| **ALL border colors** | **Primer via useTheme** | `var(--primer-border-default)`, `var(--primer-border-muted)` |
| **Overlay colors** | **Primer via useTheme** | `var(--primer-neutral-muted)` |
| **Color adjustments** | Primer tokens | Use a different `--primer-*` token (e.g., `canvas-inset` < `canvas-default` < `canvas-subtle`) |
| Typography (when custom) | Tailwind | But prefer Primer `<Text size="small">` first |
| **Reusable tokens** | **`buildThemeVars` LAYOUT_VARS** | `var(--layout-rail-width)`, `var(--rail-label-font-size)` |

### CSS Custom Properties — Single Source of Truth

All reusable CSS custom properties (layout dimensions, typography tokens, timing values) MUST be defined in `LAYOUT_VARS` inside `components-web/src/utils/theme.utils.ts`. NEVER define reusable tokens as local variables inside SCSS modules. See `design-tokens.mdc` for the full rule.

## Colors — Primer Theme via useTheme + style prop

ALL colors come from Primer's theme object via `useTheme`. Colors are injected as `--primer-*` CSS custom properties on a root wrapper using the `style` prop, then referenced in SCSS.

Primer's built-in CSS variables (e.g., `--bgColor-default`) do NOT work directly in SCSS — they are not injected into the DOM. Always use `useTheme` to bridge colors.

### The Pattern

1. **Shell module** (or top-level orchestrator) calls `useTheme` and injects `--primer-*` CSS custom properties via `style` on a wrapper:

```tsx
const { theme } = useTheme()
const themeVars = buildThemeVars(theme?.colors)

return <div style={themeVars}>{children}</div>
```

2. **All SCSS files** reference `--primer-*` for colors:

```scss
.root {
  background-color: var(--primer-canvas-default);
  color: var(--primer-fg-default);
  border: 1px solid var(--primer-border-default);
}
```

### Available --primer-* Variables

| Variable | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `--primer-fg-default` | Default text |
| `--primer-fg-muted` | Muted/secondary text |
| `--primer-fg-on-emphasis` | Text on dark backgrounds |
| `--primer-canvas-default` | Default background |
| `--primer-canvas-subtle` | Subtle/muted background |
| `--primer-canvas-inset` | Inset background |
| `--primer-border-default` | Default borders |
| `--primer-border-muted` | Subtle borders |
| `--primer-neutral-emphasis` | Neutral dark |
| `--primer-neutral-emphasis-plus` | Darkest neutral |
| `--primer-neutral-muted` | Neutral muted/overlay |
| `--primer-accent-emphasis` | Primary/accent |
| `--primer-accent-fg` | Accent foreground |
| `--primer-accent-muted` | Accent muted |
| `--primer-success-emphasis` | Success/green |
| `--primer-success-fg` | Success foreground |
| `--primer-success-muted` | Success muted |

### What is FORBIDDEN

```scss
// FORBIDDEN — Tailwind color utilities
.card { @apply bg-neutral-900 text-white; }

// FORBIDDEN — hardcoded colors
.card { color: #333; }

// FORBIDDEN — Primer CSS vars directly (they don't work)
.card { color: var(--fgColor-default); }
.card { background-color: var(--bgColor-emphasis); }

// REQUIRED — use --primer-* injected via useTheme
.card { color: var(--primer-fg-default); }
.card { background-color: var(--primer-canvas-default); }
```

**Before using arbitrary values** (e.g., `text-[0.625rem]`), ALWAYS check if the Primer component has a built-in prop. For example, use `<Text size="small">` instead of custom font sizes.

## Conditional Classes — clsx

ALWAYS use `clsx` for composing class names. NEVER use template literals, string concatenation, or `&&` short-circuit.

Use the object syntax `{ [class]: condition }` for conditional classes:

```tsx
// BAD — template literals / ternaries
<div className={`${styles.root} ${isActive ? styles.active : ''}`}>

// BAD — short-circuit (not explicit enough)
<div className={clsx(styles.root, isActive && styles.active)}>

// GOOD — object syntax for conditionals
import clsx from 'clsx'

<div className={clsx(styles.root, { [styles.active]: isActive })}>
<div className={clsx(styles.root, styles[variant])}>
```

## Zero Inline JS Styles

- NEVER use the `style` prop for layout, spacing, sizing, or visual styling
- NEVER use `sx`, `css`, or any JS-in-CSS approach
- The `style` prop is allowed ONLY for injecting Primer theme colors as `--primer-*` CSS custom properties via `useTheme` (see pattern above)

## Overriding Primer Component Styles

When Primer's built-in `variant` prop doesn't provide the needed visual (e.g., toggle buttons on dark backgrounds), use `variant="invisible"` + `className` to take full control. Double the selector for specificity to win over Primer's internal styles:

```scss
.toggleButton.toggleButton {
  background: none;
  color: var(--primer-fg-muted);
  box-shadow: none;
}

.toggleButton.toggleButton:hover {
  background: none;
  color: var(--primer-fg-default);
  box-shadow: none;
}
```

### CSS Specificity — Doubled Selectors MUST Match Everywhere

When using doubled selectors (`.foo.foo`) to override Primer, the SAME doubled pattern MUST be used in ALL contexts including media queries. A single selector in a media query CANNOT override a doubled selector.

```scss
// BAD — .backdrop in @include md loses to .backdrop.backdrop
.backdrop.backdrop { @apply block; }
@include md { .backdrop { @apply hidden; } }

// GOOD — matching specificity
.backdrop.backdrop { @apply block; }
@include md { .backdrop.backdrop { @apply hidden; } }
```

```tsx
<IconButton
  variant="invisible"
  className={styles.toggleButton}
  icon={ChevronLeftIcon}
  aria-label={t('actions.toggle')}
  onClick={onToggle}
/>
```

## No className as Prop — Variant Only (Custom Components)

Custom components NEVER accept `className`, `style`, or any styling-related prop.
The ONLY way to alter appearance is via a typed `variant` prop.
`className` is allowed ONLY when overriding third-party (Primer) components.

```tsx
import clsx from 'clsx'
import styles from './Card.module.scss'

export const Card = ({ variant, children }: CardProps) => (
  <div className={clsx(styles.root, styles[variant])}>
    {children}
  </div>
)
```

## Responsive — Mobile-First with Tailwind Breakpoints

Use mobile-first styles. Override at Tailwind breakpoints for larger screens.

In `.css` files (processed by PostCSS), use Tailwind's `screen()` function:

```css
@media screen(md) { /* 768px+ */ }
```

In `.module.scss` files, use the breakpoint mixins from `src/styles/_breakpoints.scss`:

```scss
@use '@/styles/breakpoints' as *;

.sidebar {
  @apply fixed;
}

@include md {
  .sidebar {
    @apply relative;
  }
}
```

Available mixins: `sm` (40rem), `md` (48rem), `lg` (64rem), `xl` (80rem), `xxl` (96rem).

NEVER hardcode breakpoint values in media queries — always use the mixins.
NEVER use `max-width` — write mobile-first.

## No Margin — Ever

NEVER use `margin` in any form. Use `padding` or `gap`.
Enforced by Stylelint `property-disallowed-list`.
